observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendation that management:
Maintain a ledger card for each class of Property, Plant and Equipment to support the balances presented in the FS and ensure that the basis of computation of the depreciation expenses is correct;
Prioritize the reconciliation of balances between the accounting records and RPCPPE. Prepare adjusting entries, if any, to reflect the correct balances of the affected accounts in the FS.

We recommended that management:
Identify and allocate an area to serve as a central storage for supplies to be carried in stock;

In the meantime that no central storeroom is available, require all heads of departments to designate a person within their department to act as supplies custodian who will account for all receipts and issuances using the NGAS forms prescribed for Local Government Units;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain supplies ledger cards;

Require the Accounting Office to observe perpetual inventory system in the evaluation of inventories;

Require the Inventory Team to conduct periodic inventory of supplies and render a report especially at year end;

Ensure that the year-end balances of the inventory accounts correspond to the value of supplies items, actually on hand at year end;

Establish control procedures to regulate the issuances of supplies to actual requirements of the end users within a month.
